reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Bought these to make first aid kits for the vehicles my family uses. They were cheap, so I wasn't expecting incredible quality. Like I figured, these are just okay. The first aid logo came with some loose threads, the zippers are finnicky and sticky, but they hold everything they need to and are small enough to easily fit under a car seat. I wouldn't recommend these if you plan on zipping and unzipping them frequently, the zippers seem really cheap and I wouldn't be surprised if they broke.

This bag is the perfect size to keep a decent amount of supplies in. I like the small pockets, and envelopes inside to keep things organized. The outside zipper seems very solid and i have had no issues with the zipper splitting or breaking. I keep this in the glove box of my car. I also like that its bright colour is easy to find, and even if I couldn't get to it, I could easily direct someone where to look and they would be able to find it.
Durable and good in this price
